1.1
log
@Initial revision
@
text
@Uutf is an non-blocking streaming Unicode codec for OCaml to
decode and encode the UTF-8, UTF-16, UTF-16LE and UTF-16BE
encoding schemes. It can efficiently work character by
character without blocking on IO. Decoders perform character
position tracking and support newline normalization.

Functions are also provided to fold over the characters of
UTF encoded OCaml string values and to directly encode
characters in OCaml Buffer.t values.

Uutf is made of a single, independent, module and
distributed under the BSD3 license.
@


